cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Lunheng (论衡): Multi-agent paper review framework anchored to top-tier journal rubrics"
abstract: >
  A Claude-native re-implementation and extension of the Story2Proposal
  framework. Lunheng treats paper improvement as a contract-governed
  multi-agent process: four specialist agents (Architect, Writer, Refiner,
  Evaluator-bench of 8 dimensions) coordinate around a persistent visual
  contract. Scoring uses anchored 1-10 anchors per dimension, mapped to
  actual NeurIPS 2025 / Nature / JACS reviewer rubrics.
authors:
